Step 2: 4-(4,4,5,5-tetramethyl-1,3,2-dioxaborolan-2-yl)phenethyl methanesulfonate

A mixture of 2-(4-(4,4,5,5-tetramethyl-1,3,2-dioxaborolan-2-yl)phenyl)ethan-1-ol (step 1) (100 g, 300 mmol) and TEA (240 g, 2400 mmol) in DCM (1300 ml) was stirred at 0° C. for 20 min. Then, MsCl (136 g, 1200 mmol) in DCM (200 ml) was dropwise added. After the addition, the RM was stirred at RT for 16 h. Then, the mixture was washed with water (3×300 ml), dried over Na2SO4 and concentrated under reduced pressure. Purification of the crude residue by chromatography on silica gel eluting with 0-50% EtOAc in DCM afforded 87 g of the title compound as a colorless oil.

LC-MS (Method H): Rt=1.92 min, [M+H]+=327.

A mixture of tert-butyl 3,9-diazaspiro[5.5]undecane-3-carboxylate (CAS 173405-78-2) (34 g, 133 mmol), 4-(4,4,5,5-tetramethyl-1,3,2-dioxaborolan-2-yl)phenethyl methanesulfonate (step 2) (86 g, 172 mmol), K2CO3 (47 g, 345 mmol) and KI (2.3 g, 13.8 mmol) in ACN (1000 ml) was stirred at 60° C. for 16 h. The RM was then poured into EtOAc (1500 ml), the organic layer was washed with water (100 ml), dried over Na2SO4, filtered and concentrated under reduced pressure.
